<div id="outline-container-org91a5fb1" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org91a5fb1"><span class="section-number-4">1.2.3.</span> Notes</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-2-3">
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>The original code is with BG units, and has been modified into SI units.</li>
<li>In Octave, the code needs additional data smoothing function: <code>smooth.m</code> (included in the zip file.)</li>
<li><p>
The code is a function. Inputs are
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>height</code>: wave height</li>
<li><code>period</code>: wave period</li>
<li><code>depth</code>: wave depth</li>
</ul>
<p>
Outputs are
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><code>graph</code>: the graph</li>
<li><code>xpoint</code>: the x-coordinate of the input wave condition: \(h/gT^{2}\)</li>
<li><code>ypoint</code>: the y-coordinate of the input wave condition: \(H/gT^{2}\)</li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

